How price moves up and down in Stock?

Let’s walk a **step-by-step story** showing exactly how price moves **up and down**.

---

# Scene: Market Starts (ABC Stock)

Initial order book:

BUY (Bids)          SELL (Asks)
₹99 (100)           ₹101 (100)
₹98 (200)           ₹102 (200)

👉 No trade yet
👉 Latest Price = (last traded earlier, assume ₹100)

---

# STEP 1: Buyer Becomes Aggressive → Price Goes UP

### Ravi says:

> “Buy 100 shares at ₹101”

---

## What happens?

* Best SELL = ₹101
* Ravi is ready to pay ₹101

👉 Match happens!

---

## Trade:

* 100 shares @ ₹101

👉 **Latest Price = ₹101**

---

## Why price went UP?

Because:

> Buyer accepted higher price

---

# STEP 2: More Aggressive Buyers → Price keeps rising

### Another buyer:

> “Buy 200 shares at ₹102”

---

## Match:

* 100 shares @ ₹102
* Remaining 100 shares also matched at ₹102

👉 **Latest Price = ₹102**

---

## Insight

> Buyers are “lifting” prices by accepting higher asks

---

# STEP 3: Seller Becomes Aggressive → Price Goes DOWN

Now situation changes.

### Sita says:

> “Sell 150 shares at ₹99”

---

## What happens?

* Best BUY = ₹99
* Sita agrees to ₹99

👉 Match!

---

## Trade:

* 150 shares @ ₹99

👉 **Latest Price = ₹99**

---

## Why price went DOWN?

Because:

> Seller accepted lower price

---

# STEP 4: Panic Selling → Price Drops Fast

### Many sellers:

> “Sell at ANY price” (market orders)

---

## Matching:

* Match with ₹99
* Then ₹98
* Then ₹97 (if exists)

---

👉 Trades happen at lower and lower prices

👉 **Price keeps falling**

---

## Insight

> Aggressive sellers push price DOWN

---

# STEP 5: Balanced Market → Price Stable

If:

* Buyers at ₹100
* Sellers at ₹101

👉 No one agrees

👉 No trades

👉 Price stays around last value

---

# CORE TRUTH (Very Important)

Price does NOT move randomly
It moves because of:

Aggressive Buyers → Price UP
Aggressive Sellers → Price DOWN

---

# Full Micro Flow (Real Engine View)

### Case: Price goes UP

New BUY order (high price)
→ Matches SELL
→ Trade at higher price
→ LTP increases

---

### Case: Price goes DOWN

New SELL order (low price)
→ Matches BUY
→ Trade at lower price
→ LTP decreases

---

# Visual Intuition

## 📈 Price goes UP when:

* Buyers say: “I’ll pay MORE”

## Price goes DOWN when:

* Sellers say: “I’ll accept LESS”

---

# One-Line Memory

> “Price moves in the direction of urgency — whoever is more desperate controls the price.”

---

# C++ Mental Mapping

In your engine:

if (buy.price >= sell.price) {
    trade.price = sell.price; // or matching rule
    lastPrice = trade.price;
}

👉 That single line is what moves the market.

